import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.countplot(x='job', data=data, palette='viridis')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.xlabel('Job Title')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of job titles in the dataset?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    gender_count = data.groupby('sex').size().reset_index(name='count')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.pie(gender_count['count'], labels=gender_count['sex'], autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90, colors=['#ff9999','#66b3ff'])
    ax.axis('equal')
    plt.title('What is the gender distribution in the dataset?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    plt.figure(figsize=(12,8))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='count', hue='job', data=data, ci=None)
    plt.title('How has the count of individuals in each job title changed over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.legend(loc='upper left', bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby(['job', 'sex']).sum().reset_index()
    data['perc'] = data.groupby('job')['count'].apply(lambda x: x / x.sum())
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    sns.barplot(x="job", y="perc", hue="sex", data=data)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.xlabel('Job Title')
    plt.ylabel('Percentage')
    plt.title('What is the percentage of men and women in each job title?')
    plt.legend(title='Gender', loc='upper right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='perc', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['perc'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['perc'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of percentage values in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Percentage')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
